The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) Makurdi zonal office has nabbed the clerk of the Benue State House of Assembly, Torese Agena, for alleged fraud, stealing and misappropriation of public funds. Head of Public Affairs EFCC zonal office, Nwanyinma Okeanu, in a statement accused him of embezzling money to the tune of over Two hundred and twenty million Naira (N220,000,000). According to her,  the suspected clerk is currently in EFCC custody on a valid remand warrant obtained from the Federal High Court, Makurdi. She disclosed that the wife of the Clerk Terngu and her daughters, Terfa – Mamadu Ngueavese and Agena Suur on getting the information came to the EFCC office and assaulted two mobile policemen on duty. The wife of the suspect came with her children to the office and physically assaulted the two policemen on duty while  the third one was given a human bite on his left arm, and also tried to run down the other with their car while trying to escape According to her, the suspect’s wife as well as her two daughters who carried out the assault have been handed over to the police for onward prosecution. She further disclosed that while the clerk’s arraignment is being processed for onwards  prosecution as soon as investigation is concluded. When contacted the Police Public Relations Officer DSP Catherine Anene said she is yet to receive the suspects.